<section id="intro" class="section active">
  <div class="hero" style="margin:-60px -60px 40px; padding:60px;">
    <div class="hero-tag">Unit I — Fundamentals</div>
    <h2>Introduction to<br><span>Data Structures</span></h2>
    <p>A complete interactive guide covering theory, pseudocode, and C++ implementations with live visualizations.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card-grid">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-icon">📦</div>
      <h3>What is a Data Structure?</h3>
      <p>A data structure is a way of organizing and storing data in a computer so that it can be accessed and modified efficiently.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-icon">⚙️</div>
      <h3>What is an Algorithm?</h3>
      <p>A step-by-step procedure or set of rules for solving a specific problem. Algorithms manipulate data in data structures.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-icon">🔗</div>
      <h3>Relationship: Data → DS → Algo</h3>
      <p>Data is organized using Data Structures. Algorithms operate on these structures. Together they form efficient programs.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3 style="font-family:'Syne',sans-serif; font-size:20px; margin:32px 0 16px;">Types of Data Structures</h3>
  <div class="card-grid">
    <div class="card" style="border-color:rgba(0,212,255,0.2)">
      <div class="card-icon">📋</div>
      <h3 style="color:var(--accent)">Primitive</h3>
      <p>int, float, char, double — basic types directly supported by hardware/OS.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="border-color:rgba(124,58,237,0.2)">
      <div class="card-icon">🔢</div>
      <h3 style="color:#a78bfa">Linear (Non-Primitive)</h3>
      <p>Elements arranged sequentially. Array, Stack, Queue, Linked List.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="border-color:rgba(16,185,129,0.2)">
      <div class="card-icon">🌲</div>
      <h3 style="color:var(--accent3)">Non-Linear</h3>
      <p>Elements not in sequence. Trees, Graphs — hierarchical/network relationships.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="border-color:rgba(245,158,11,0.2)">
      <div class="card-icon">📁</div>
      <h3 style="color:var(--accent4)">File Structures</h3>
      <p>Data stored in secondary memory. Sequential, Direct, Index-Sequential.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

