<!-- ======================== COMPLEXITY ======================== -->
<section id="complexity" class="section">
  <div class="section-badge badge-yellow">Analysis</div>
  <h2>Algorithm Complexity</h2>
  <p>Measuring how efficient an algorithm is in terms of time and space as input size grows.</p>

  <div class="card-grid">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-icon">⏱</div>
      <h3>Time Complexity</h3>
      <p>The amount of time taken by an algorithm as a function of input size <code style="color:var(--accent);font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;">n</code>. Counts number of operations.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-icon">💾</div>
      <h3>Space Complexity</h3>
      <p>The total amount of memory space required (including auxiliary space) as a function of input size.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3 style="font-family:'Syne',sans-serif; font-size:20px; margin:32px 0 16px;">Asymptotic Notations</h3>
  <div class="card-grid">
    <div class="card" style="border-color:rgba(16,185,129,0.2)">
      <h3 style="color:var(--accent3)">O (Big-O) — Upper Bound</h3>
      <p>Worst-case scenario. f(n) = O(g(n)) means f grows no faster than g.</p>
      <div style="margin-top:10px; font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace; font-size:13px; color:var(--accent3);">Example: O(n²) for bubble sort</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="border-color:rgba(0,212,255,0.2)">
      <h3 style="color:var(--accent)">Ω (Omega) — Lower Bound</h3>
      <p>Best-case scenario. f(n) = Ω(g(n)) means f grows at least as fast as g.</p>
      <div style="margin-top:10px; font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace; font-size:13px; color:var(--accent);">Example: Ω(n) for linear search</div>
    </div>
    <div class="card" style="border-color:rgba(124,58,237,0.2)">
      <h3 style="color:#a78bfa">Θ (Theta) — Tight Bound</h3>
      <p>Average-case. f(n) = Θ(g(n)) when both upper and lower bounds are g.</p>
      <div style="margin-top:10px; font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace; font-size:13px; color:#a78bfa;">Example: Θ(n log n) for merge sort</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3 style="font-family:'Syne',sans-serif; font-size:20px; margin:32px 0 16px;">Complexity Hierarchy</h3>
  <div style="background:var(--code-bg); border-radius:8px; padding:20px;">
