  <div id="sort-tab">
    <div id="sort-bubble" class="tab-content active">
      <div class="highlight-box">
        <h4>💭 Bubble Sort — Theory</h4>
        <p>Repeatedly swap adjacent elements that are in wrong order. Largest element "bubbles up" to end each pass. Optimized version stops early if no swaps in a pass.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="code-block">
        <div class="code-header"><div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;"><div class="code-dots"><div class="code-dot dot-r"></div><div class="code-dot dot-y"></div><div class="code-dot dot-g"></div></div><span>bubble_sort.cpp</span></div><button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyCode(this)">copy</button></div>
        <pre><span class="kw">void</span> <span class="fn">bubbleSort</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> arr[], <span class="kw">int</span> n) {
    <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> i = <span class="num">0</span>; i < n-<span class="num">1</span>; i++) {
        <span class="kw">bool</span> swapped = <span class="kw">false</span>;
        <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> j = <span class="num">0</span>; j < n-i-<span class="num">1</span>; j++) {
            <span class="kw">if</span>(arr[j] > arr[j+<span class="num">1</span>]) {
                swap(arr[j], arr[j+<span class="num">1</span>]);
                swapped = <span class="kw">true</span>;
            }
        }
        <span class="kw">if</span>(!swapped) <span class="kw">break</span>; <span class="cm">// already sorted</span>
    }
}
<span class="cm">// Time: O(n²) avg/worst  | Space: O(1)</span></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="sort-insertion" class="tab-content">
      <div class="highlight-box">
        <h4>💭 Insertion Sort — Theory</h4>
        <p>Like sorting playing cards in hand. Pick one card at a time and insert it in correct position among already-sorted cards. Efficient for nearly-sorted arrays.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="code-block">
        <div class="code-header"><div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;"><div class="code-dots"><div class="code-dot dot-r"></div><div class="code-dot dot-y"></div><div class="code-dot dot-g"></div></div><span>insertion_sort.cpp</span></div><button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyCode(this)">copy</button></div>
        <pre><span class="kw">void</span> <span class="fn">insertionSort</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> arr[], <span class="kw">int</span> n) {
    <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> i = <span class="num">1</span>; i < n; i++) {
        <span class="kw">int</span> key = arr[i];
        <span class="kw">int</span> j = i - <span class="num">1</span>;
        <span class="cm">// shift elements greater than key</span>
        <span class="kw">while</span>(j >= <span class="num">0</span> && arr[j] > key) {
            arr[j+<span class="num">1</span>] = arr[j];
            j--;
        }
        arr[j+<span class="num">1</span>] = key; <span class="cm">// place key in correct spot</span>
    }
}
<span class="cm">// Time: O(n) best, O(n²) avg/worst | Space: O(1)</span></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="sort-selection" class="tab-content">
      <div class="highlight-box">
        <h4>💭 Selection Sort — Theory</h4>
        <p>Find the minimum element in unsorted portion and swap it to the front. Simple but always O(n²) — never better than worst case.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="code-block">
        <div class="code-header"><div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;"><div class="code-dots"><div class="code-dot dot-r"></div><div class="code-dot dot-y"></div><div class="code-dot dot-g"></div></div><span>selection_sort.cpp</span></div><button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyCode(this)">copy</button></div>
        <pre><span class="kw">void</span> <span class="fn">selectionSort</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> arr[], <span class="kw">int</span> n) {
    <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> i = <span class="num">0</span>; i < n-<span class="num">1</span>; i++) {
        <span class="kw">int</span> minIdx = i;
        <span class="cm">// find minimum in unsorted portion</span>
        <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> j = i+<span class="num">1</span>; j < n; j++)
            <span class="kw">if</span>(arr[j] < arr[minIdx]) minIdx = j;
        swap(arr[i], arr[minIdx]); <span class="cm">// place min at front</span>
    }
}
<span class="cm">// Time: O(n²) always | Space: O(1)</span></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="sort-quick" class="tab-content">
      <div class="highlight-box">
        <h4>💭 Quick Sort — Theory</h4>
        <p>Divide and conquer. Choose a pivot, partition array so elements less than pivot go left, greater go right. Recursively sort partitions. Average O(n log n) but O(n²) worst case.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="code-block">
        <div class="code-header"><div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;"><div class="code-dots"><div class="code-dot dot-r"></div><div class="code-dot dot-y"></div><div class="code-dot dot-g"></div></div><span>quick_sort.cpp</span></div><button class="copy-btn" onclick="copyCode(this)">copy</button></div>
        <pre><span class="kw">int</span> <span class="fn">partition</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> arr[], <span class="kw">int</span> low, <span class="kw">int</span> high) {
    <span class="kw">int</span> pivot = arr[high]; <span class="cm">// last element as pivot</span>
    <span class="kw">int</span> i = low - <span class="num">1</span>;       <span class="cm">// smaller element index</span>
    <span class="kw">for</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> j = low; j < high; j++) {
        <span class="kw">if</span>(arr[j] <= pivot) {
            i++;
            swap(arr[i], arr[j]);
        }
    }
    swap(arr[i+<span class="num">1</span>], arr[high]); <span class="cm">// place pivot correctly</span>
    <span class="kw">return</span> i + <span class="num">1</span>;
}

<span class="kw">void</span> <span class="fn">quickSort</span>(<span class="kw">int</span> arr[], <span class="kw">int</span> low, <span class="kw">int</span> high) {
    <span class="kw">if</span>(low < high) {
        <span class="kw">int</span> pi = <span class="fn">partition</span>(arr, low, high);
        <span class="fn">quickSort</span>(arr, low, pi - <span class="num">1</span>);
        <span class="fn">quickSort</span>(arr, pi + <span class="num">1</span>, high);
    }
}
<span class="cm">// Time: O(n log n) avg | O(n²) worst | Space: O(log n)</span></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

